<br>
If my macros offend anyone in my group, I can remove the /g statements and they can try to figure out what the heck I'm doing.  But they better not...<br>
<br>
...assist me while I'm doing CC (happens a lot)<br>
...hit something I just mezzed (happens a lot too)<br>
...wonder why there are no bard songs while I'm doing CC (can buff or CC, not both if pulls are 3+)<br>
...complain that some spell won't because of my songs (some bard songs will not stack ie: snare/chains)<br>
...yell at me for hitting the wrong target when I clearly assisted the tank and he/she switched targets without telling the group<br>
<br>
I group with strangers a lot.  They don't know me, I don't know them.  I wanna know what they are doing, and in return I tell them what I'm doing.  Like I said in an earlier post, I'm a lowbie...so the game I play is a LOT different from what most of you folk play.  In the game I play, macros are helpful.<br>
<br>
And considering some of the commentary, maybe it's a good thing I'm still a lowbie.  I apparently suck as my sig line suggests anyway...<br>
<br>
